reviews.review_text:
Saint Stephen Just came across the Saint Stephen jam within the Jam after Alligator and Drums.

About 38 years ago I used to listen to a bootleg album that had this Second That Emotion, New Minglewood and Cold Rain and Snow. I still have that vinyl.

Ron's organ is so clear - this is a great mix from one of the band's best years
The obvious attraction here is the Alligator/GDTR/Cold Rain, but the era of great Alligator jams was over by this point.

finale Cumberland and the "jam" are the highlights for me here.

Here are some other excellent '71 versions.

Sugar Mag 2/18
Loser 4/10
Bertha 4/13
Casey Jones 4/17
Morning Dew 4/28
Brokedown 8/14
Playing 11/7
Black Peter 12/09
